I do not play a wiz, but I always hear people complain about the huge increase in power wiz get in pop. Just from pop AA abilities plus gear how much of a dps increase did wiz get. I always thought a wiz best damage/mana ratio spell is a lvl 60 spell, so where did all this increase  dps come from.  <br>
<br>
My first character was a wiz way back in kunark,  and I want to know can a wiz with vt gear have the same dps  as a ranger or rogue or even a bl in a zero down time grp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 387<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 5:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much of a dps inc did wiz get with pop</span><hr size=1> the very short POP boss mob fights are where a lot of the power increases are found. as groups go, a zero downtime group means that your wizard's dps will approach the limit of his sustained dps(theoretically). it's simple to take my average mana/tick (56) and multiply that by my average of doi/isos efficiencies(9.07 off the top of my head, but might be thinking of 15% pres when I have 20%). My 6k mana pool's dps in a 0-downtime group will eventually go lower and lower - eventually being minimal at huge amts of time.<br>
<br>
mana rate * efficiency = sustained dps<br>
(56/6)*9.07 = 84.6dps<br>
with meditation/standrate<br>
(80/6)*9.07 = 121dps<br>
so you produce a range of sustained dps between 84.6 - 121. naturally, you're not medding all the time(you do nuke and move) so your sustained dps should fall anywhere between these two numbers: without resists present.<br>
<br>
I see rogues in BOT doing 150dps with piercers and 150/84.6 = 23% - 77.3% more damage than a wizard. when uptime is considered, divide the sustained dps figure by the uptime figure and this will give you the `comparative` sustained dps that you should be applying to the target. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Has Eddie Murphy's<BR>taste in women</span><br>  Posts: 3751<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 5:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much of a dps inc did wiz get with pop</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>My first character was a wiz way back in kunark, and I want to know can a wiz with vt gear have the same dps as a ranger or rogue or even a bl in a zero down time grp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wizard &gt; ranger<br>
Wizard ~= rogue<br>
Wizard &gt;&gt;&gt; beastlord<br>
<br>
however, typically<br>
<br>
Mage &gt; wizard; but it's not a major difference.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I do not play a wiz, but I always hear people complain about the huge increase in power wiz get in pop. Just from pop AA abilities plus gear how much of a dps increase did wiz get. I always thought a wiz best damage/mana ratio spell is a lvl 60 spell, so where did all this increase dps come from.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
DPS figures are always sketchy at best.  There's no concrete &quot;class y gained x dps&quot; math out there, but we did get a pretty spectacular power gain with PoP, from our draught series (~3.8 ratio with a -50 resist check, meaning they almost always hit w/o debuffs), to Strike of Solusek (combined with elemental gloves, which have a focus effect reducing the mana cost on SoS by 25%) you get something like a 5.0 ratio, to Iceflame of E'Ci, a spell which acts as a 30% damage increase to level 60 cold spells <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stacks with focus items, yielding a maximum of a 6.0 ratio.  We have the best self-only mana buffs which stack with almost everything; simply put, we get more mana regen than other classes can when fully buffed.<br>
<br>
The old &quot;wizards can't keep up in xp groups&quot; myth is long dead, except to board trolls and wizards who just like to bitch a lot because their poor social skills preclude them from finding groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1926<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 5:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much of a dps inc did wiz get with pop</span><hr size=1> With spells like SoS and AT and all that spell haste now our burst DPS increased incredibly. And with warrior hate blow weapons being more avialble now our sustained raid DPS also got a huge increasement <p>Sage Quineloe<br>
