<br>
<br>
Mana regen -&gt; spell efficiency -&gt; speciallization -&gt; MP focus -&gt; ID focus -&gt; crits<br>
<br>
<br>
Mana regen: Improved spells from buffers, FT items, familiars, harvest / HoD, mana regen AAs.<br>
<br>
Spell efficiency: Level 61+ spells, naturally, get more efficient (in general).<br>
<br>
Speciallization: Spec-Evoc 200 is a given.  SCM also fits in here for another 10%.<br>
<br>
MP Focus: Lots of nice focus items out there, although mage goodies are still a favorite.<br>
<br>
ID Focus: Finally, some cool Improved Damage focus items (although I have no clue how available they are).  Also, Iceflame is a nice focus buff.<br>
<br>
Crit AA: Wizard have more levels of crits available to them than any other class, I believe.  From what I've read, at maxed level, they're worth a 20% increase in damage. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
