<br>
We all know that Velious completely screwed the wizard class with the lack of new spells and in general more boosts to melees.  Flowing thoughts FINALLY got added, but very few items and far between to get them.<br>
<br>
Luclin fixed a lot of the design problems that wizards had with the addition of AA abilities.  It might take getting 30+ AA points, but melees got relatively few upgrades.  The wizard spells were pretty much impossible for those outside of the high level uber and demi-uber guilds to get, so again, no spell upgrades to boost wizard damage output for MOST wizards, but the AA abilities, additional flowing thoughts items, and eventually(8 months) after launch we got focus items.<br>
<br>
After Luclin, Wizards were more or less balanced against melees.  With PoP, they FINALLY got it right, they boosted casting classes fairly compared to the melee classes.  Wizards got spells that were actually obtainable by the majority of wizards, even if it's taking a while, Agnarr's Thunder is in the 5 to 6k range in bazaar on my server.  Even without Strike of Solusek, we saw a nice boost in power.  <br>
<br>
To be honest, the only real area I see melees complaining about is warriors not being able to taunt as well as most feel they should be able to.  Yes, there are some items that boost taunt, but warriors could use some more benefits in the taunt department.  Aside from that, PoP is a remarkably balanced expansion when it comes to abilities and loot.  Those who complain about wizards getting more powerful are only looking at it as &quot;How much did wizards get since Velious&quot;, not, &quot;How well balanced is the class on the whole&quot;.  Wizards are SUPPOSED to be dealers of massive levels of damage.  It takes wizards the longest to come into our power, so it makes sense that we are the BIG GUNS at level 65 with good equipment.<br>
<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 65 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
