</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1381<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 4:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> Dps is being used confusingly here. I'd rather use dph for sustained dmg potential since that wont vary much with downtime. Dps varies hugely for casters minute by minute.<br>
<br>
In fact, the biggest boost casters have got with pop isnt from ft, focus or spells, it's that group average downtime has gone up *hugely* as compared with luclin. It's always preferable to harmony/pacify single pull wherever possible, and the odd death per hour (to others <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) doesnt harm our dps either.<br>
<br>
If we really are talking max dps improvement, well SoS and SoM provide a big boost, but a bigger boost in practice is from the better aggro tanks have these days than ever before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1036<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 4:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>...but a bigger boost in practice is from the better aggro tanks have these days than ever before.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Arguable. First off, the worst taunter these days are Warriors. Their taunt need an huge upgrade (in exp groups, not talking about AE taunt.) SKs, Pallies, even Rangers hold aggro so much better than Wariors.<br>
<br>
Second, our PoP nukes generate much much more aggro than pre PoP, compensating for the new taunt abbiliites of SKs and Pallies. (Maybe this was done to encourage us to invest time and AA points into the SCS skill.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blaloceanos>Blal Oceanos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Heart-Shaped Armadillo</span><br>  Posts: 740<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 5:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> with just grouping u can obtain FT4-7 depending how lucky u are.<br>
<br>
Boots of Flowing Slime and Soltice Earing are easy to get if your commited enough to getting them.<br>
<br>
PoP has a few droppable FT things runnin around, but kinda rare.<br>
<br>
Mana pool, your looking in the 4000 unbuffed area, for unuber.<br>
<br>
This game rewards how much time u put into it. If u spend a lot of time xping and collecting cash then you will have better stats than if u dont. Casual people complain because theyre not as desirable in groups as a hardcore player, which i think is stupid because the hardcore player has put more time into the game so therefore should get more out of it.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://cr0m.homestead.com/files/wb3d.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51599"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Sage Blal Oceanos</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->65 Arcanist </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 619<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 6:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I havnt done any number crunching, and using my own toon is a poor example I suppose as I dont have many AA's and my gear is pretty dated.<br>
<br>
But, even with my setup I can keep up in most group situations without finding myself tapped and able to maintain a descent DPS.<br>
<br>
Are wizards the best at substained DPS vs a top rouge? meh, probably not. I havnt done any parsing but by going by the numbers someone else posted of him doing 88-120dps and a rogue doing 150.. I dont see any problems with that. Rogues also need to deal with melee range (downfall in raids), dont have some of the utility we do .. and, our 'burst' DPS is better.<br>
<br>
With focus items, my SoS regullarly goes over 3k. Not inlcuding haste items (to lazy to do that math), 3k/10secs = 300dps theoriticly. Toss in a concussion after every spell (if your being anal and feel like killing your DPS) and it lowers it to like, 214dps. .. and that is with lazy numbers (on debuffed mobs, my SoS hits for more then 3k, with haste/etc, my cast time is less then 8 seconds + 2 sec refresh/etc). Toss in crits/etc, and we are pretty well off. Now, if a wizard is lucky enough to have concussion pants, that just makes things even better. No need to wait for the 2sec+2sec refresh cast time of casting concussion.<br>
<br>
Being able to hold our own (if even not 'the best' compared to some classess) at substianed DPS in a group and having a considerbly nice burst damage when needed and in raid situations, I'm pretty happy with the damage aspects of the class.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1382<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 6:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> Dunno about you Natan but the MT on 95% of our raids is a warrior, and warriors arent worse off for aggro than they were a year ago, how could they be - existing aggro weapons havent been removed from the game, actually more have been added. So on raids I'm doing more dps before getting aggro than pre-pop.<br>
<br>
In terms of xp groups, hybrids are much more common than they were pre-pop so my max dps is higher there too. Actually it's much much higher since SoS and AT are much more available than GSS and ERR were.<br>
<br>
So, in summary, both on raids and in groups my burst dps before getting aggro is much higher than in was pre-pop. And that's all that really matters not theoretical max dps's<br>
<br>
In terms of max dph my dmg is much higher there too with the improved efficiency of SoS, Iceflame, new focuses, aa flappy 2, HoD, new mind candies etc etc.<br>
<br>
All good stuff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Owned by Ikeya<BR>Destroying EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7316<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 7:39 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DPS</span><hr size=1> For those that don't have SoS / Agnarr's (or do, btw Agnarr's is pretty easy to get) Draughts rock.  Our DPS increased quite a bit in PoP.  Claud is also correct, no Wizard at any level after 44 with any amount of AE sucks in groups. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458434" target="top">Rombus, Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702" target="top">Rommy, Archon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:<br>
